node.text:
@lethalshooter and designer @tate.kuerbis keep it light and breakdown the innovative features behind the Air Jordan 36. From borrowed features from past silhouettes to the fine details of how these shoes keep you weightless on the court. 
Make sure to get notified at the link in our bio when they drop. #ItsLightWork

node.text: In our last episodes covering voting in the 2020 election, our guests came through and dropped knowledge on how we can work together to bring positive change to our communities. Now hear from them on how we need to continue to push to make a difference beyond the election.

This week on Jordan Real Talk, @AngelaRye, @Baratunde, and guests @hfelton8711 and @MrDavidJohns discuss educational inequality, the issues of school funding, and the importance of Black educators. 

Dr. Felton and David Johns take a deeper dive into how to get involved with education reform, and why local elections are so critical to supporting the educational needs of their community.

node.title: EPISODE 3: HOW TO REFORM OUR EDUCATION SYSTEM

In this week’s episode of Jordan Real Talk, @FatJoe and @Baratunde sit down with host @AngelaRye to discuss the criminal justice system and why reform needs to take place now.

Fat Joe and Baratunde go over the movement to restore voting rights for the incarcerated & formerly incarcerated, and the topics of defunding, and reallocating resources for the community.

For this week’s episode of Jordan Real Talk, @CP3 and @Baratunde sit down with host @AngelaRye to discuss a topic that is top of everyone’s mind, voting.

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Airing October 7, Jordan Real Talk, Jordan Brand’s new content series, will highlight key issues facing the Black Community and how to drive actionable solutions.

Hosted by social commentator Angela Rye, Jordan Real Talk provides a platform for education and action through conversations featuring Jordan family athletes and influencers, journalists, social justice experts and community activists.

Head to our story to subscribe for the latest episodes.

@naacp_ldf @blackvotersmtr

node.text:
@lethalshooter and designer @tate.kuerbis keep it light and breakdown the innovative features behind the Air Jordan 36. From borrowed features from past silhouettes to the fine details of how these shoes keep you weightless on the court. 
Make sure to get notified at the link in our bio when they drop. #ItsLightWork

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jordan on August 24, 2021 tagging @jaytatum0, and @satou_sabally. May be an image of one or more people and text.

node.text:
@Satou_Sabally and @Jaytatum0 are a blur on the court. By the time you figure out if they are flashing to the rim or rising up for a jumper, it’s already too late. 
Keep up with the blistering pace, and get notified when new Air Jordan 36 colorways drop in the Nike App. #ItsLightWork

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jordan on August 23, 2021 tagging @jelaniaryeh, and @hairjordan16. May be an image of 2 people, child, footwear and text that says 'AIR'.

node.text:
“Jordan reminds me to keep a sense of awe and childlike wonder, as well as courage.” 
Growing up in San Diego, brothers @jelaniaryeh and @hairjordan16 love for football and music is what kept them inseparable. Read more about their brotherhood and where they plan to rock the new Air Jordan I Low at the link in our bio.

node.text:
From the family.
Inspired by precious gifts handed down to @AlealiMay through both her Black and Filipina sides of the family, her new Air Jordan 14 takes a brilliant new form.
Make sure to get notified in SNKRS when these drop.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jordan on August 17, 2021 tagging @joehaden23. May be an image of 2 people and child.

node.text:
@JoeHaden23 hypes his boys up and makes sure they’re prepped for school this year. They know their colors, got their books packed, and they even know the teacher’s name already.
Watch the full video of Joe’s family at the link in our bio.

It’s light work.
Blow-by, takeoff, snatch-back, elevate, dominate. Your bag is bottomless in these shoes and the quickness is at a level that can’t be clocked.
Swipe through to get a closer look at the Air Jordan 36, and learn more at the link in our bio. #ItsLightWork

node.text:
“My grandmother on my dad’s side gifted me gold and jade bangles that she’d had for 20 years before that. My grandmother on my mom’s side also gifted me her jade bangles. Those were my first pieces of jewelry.”
We spoke with @AlealiMay about her latest Jordan collab, inspired by her Black and Filipina family roots and the precious gifts passed down to her.
Read more at the link in our bio.
